<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THESE ARE THE BOOKS THAT OPRAH LOVES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I don't have a computer. Where can I get a copy of the books
chosen for Oprah's Book Club?
</P>
<P>
   _M.T., Shrewsbury, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: Since beginning the club in September 1996, Oprah Winfrey has
made the following selections on her talk show:
</P>
<P>
   ``The Deep End of the Ocean'' by Jacquelyn Mitchard, ``Song of
Solomon'' by Toni Morrison and ``The Book of Ruth'' by Jane
Hamilton.
</P>
<P>
   1997: ``She's Come Undone'' by Wally Lamb, ``Stones From the
River'' by Ursula Hegi, ``The Rapture of Canaan'' by Sheri
Reynolds, ``The Heart of a Woman'' by Maya Angelou, ``Songs in
Ordinary Time'' by Mary McGarry Morris, ``A Lesson Before Dying''
by Ernest J. Gaines, ``A Virtuous Woman'' and ``Ellen Foster'' by
Kaye Gibbons, and ``The Best Way to Play,'' ``The Treasure Hunt''
and ``The Meanest Thing to Say'' by Bill Cosby.
</P>
<P>
   1998: ``Paradise'' by Toni Morrison, ``Here on Earth'' by Alice
Hoffman, ``Black and Blue'' by Anna Quindlen, ``Breath, Eyes,
Memory'' by Edwidge Danticat, ``I Know This Much is True'' by Wally
Lamb, ``What Looks Like Crazy on an Ordinary Day'' by Pearl Cleage,
``Midwives'' by Chris Bohjalian and ``Where the Heart Is'' by
Billie Letts.
</P>
<P>
   1999: ``Jewel'' by Bret Lott, ``The Reader'' by Bernhard
Schlink, ``The Pilot's Wife'' by Anita Shreve, ``White Oleander''
by Janet Fitch and ``Mother of Pearl'' by Melinda Haynes.
</P>
<P>
   Internet users can get the list and discuss club selections by
visiting www.oprah.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is it true that Stephen Tompkinson, who played Father Peter
on the BBC TV series ``Ballykissangel'' died?
</P>
<P>
   _S.J., Worcester, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: The 33-year-old British actor is filming episodes of the TV
series ``Grafters'' and will be starting on ``Ted and Alice'' in
September, according to his official Web site.
</P>
<P>
   You can visit it at www.becks.inuk.com, and write to him in care
of Barry Brown and Partner, 47 West Square, London, England, SE11
4SP.
</P>
<P>
   Another cast member of ``Ballykissangel,'' the actor Birdy
Sweeney, died in March at age 68. He portrayed Eamon Byrne on the
show, and also appeared in the films ``The Crying Game'' and ``Moll
Flanders.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Ralph Emery of The Nashville Network?
</P>
<P>
   _D.R., Everman, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Emery in care of TNN, 2806 Opryland Drive,
Nashville, TN 37214. Emery, 66, hosted ``Nashville Now'' from 1983
to 1993 and produces a series of occasional specials titled ``Ralph
Emery on the Record.'' His third book, ``The View from Nashville,''
was released last fall.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is there a list of worldwide bed and breakfasts?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.P., Forest Hill, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: One book to consider is ``Complete Guide to Bed &AMP; Breakfasts,
Inns &AMP; Guesthouses'' by Pamela Lanier. The 1999 edition includes
22,000 listings in the U.S., Canada and other countries.
</P>
<P>
   Lanier Publishing also offers a database at
www.travelguides.com. You can search by city or country, and make
bookings online.
</P>
<P>
   If you can't find ``Complete Guide'' at a bookstore, you should
be able to special order it using ISBN 1-58008-028-6.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How much older is Juliet Mills than her sister Hayley?
</P>
<P>
   _ K.R., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Juliet Mills, 57, is four years older than Hayley. They're
part of a theatrical family that includes a screenwriter, brother
Jonathan Mills, and an Oscar-winning actor, father Sir John Mills.
</P>
<P>
   The sisters haven't worked on a project together for 52 years,
according to the Internet Movie Database at www.imdb.com. They both
appeared in the 1947 film ``So Well Remembered,'' though Hayley's
role as ``Infant'' was uncredited.
</P>
<P>
   They've stayed close otherwise. ``I'm extremely lucky that my
best friend is my sister,'' Hayley Mills told the Minneapolis
Star-Tribune in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Juliet Mills has been married since 1980 to actor Maxwell
Caulfield, 39. In 1998, Hayley ended a 13-year-relationship with
Caulfield's brother, Marcus Maclaine, 36.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
