fortunes of the 218-year-old Massachusetts Medical Society depend
on the renowned New England Journal of Medicine and, to a much
smaller extent, a dozen newer, lesser-known periodicals. By Richard
A. Knox. 1520 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   SOCIETY-TALENT (Undated) _ Time was, people consciously sought
talents as a form of personal investment. But in an era of passive
entertainment, that sort of personal improvement seems unimportant.
By Scot Lehigh. 1660 words.
</P>
