u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUD     08-03 0349
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Entertainment and culture stories from The N.Y. Times News
Service for Wednesday, Aug. 4.
</P>
<P>
   BRIDGE-OPERA (Ann Arbor, Mich.) _ On the making of a new opera
by William Bolcom, ``A View From the Bridge.'' By Bruce Weber.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   GEORGIA-EXHIBIT (Undated) _ Internal politics in the Republic of
Georgia, which faces parliamentary elections in October and a
presidential poll in April, have scuttled a landmark traveling
exhibition of Georgian gold and silver objects, illustrated
manuscripts, religious icons and other art that was due in the
United States this fall. By Judith H. Dobrzynski.
</P>
<P>
   ASPEN-MUSIC (Aspen, Colo.) _ A Critic's Notebook on summer
concerts of the Aspen Music Festival and School. By James R.
Oestreich.
</P>
