   CONNECTICUT-GUNS. Rep. Rosa DeLauro, D-New Haven, joined other
Democratic members of congress today vowing to fight Republican
assertions that background checks at gun shows will not become law.
</P>
<P>
   (600 words) By Jill Carroll
</P>
<P>
   ILLINOIS-HASTERT-PAC. House Speaker Dennis Hastert made like
Santa Claus in the first six months of 1999, giving out more than
$700,000 through his leadership political action committee. Among
the biggest beneficiaries were several congressmen who managed the
impeachment case against President Clinton. (400 words) By Mark
Stricherz
</P>
<P>
   NEW MEXICO-HATE. New Mexico House members' response to the Hate
Crimes Prevention Act, which will see a hearing in the House on
Wednesday. By Jonathan Lipman
