lobbying to restore funding to the Institute for American Indian
Arts to the House Interior Appropriations bill. The Senate version
already includes the requested $4.25 million. By Jonathan Lipman
</P>
<P>
   OHIO-BROWN-SPEND. Although it isn't even an election year, Rep.
Sherrod Brown, already has more than $800,000 to spend on his
upcoming campaign. (300 words) By Sean Gorman.
</P>
<P>
   SPACE-BUDGET. The current status of the NASA budget battle. By
Jonathan Lipman
</P>
<P>
   SPACE-TEXAS. A look at the role and work of the Texas Aerospace
Council and how well it gets along with its boss -- Republican
presidential front-runner George W. Bush. By Ted Monoson
</P>
<P>
   SPACE-X-33. What work is the Antelope Valley area doing to
attract the X-33 successor project VentureStar? By Matt Swenson
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-COOL. To help Wisconsinites battle the brutal heat,
the Badger State will get $4.4 million from the Department of
Health and Human Services, President Clinton announced Tuesday.
(400 words) By Lacy O'Toole
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-WELFARE-BALDWIN. Reps. Tammy Baldwin, D-Madison, and
Tom Barrett, D-Milwaukee, have some doubts about calling welfare
reform a success just because there is a decrease in the number of
welfare recipients. Therefore, the lawmakers are trying to pass a
measure that would require the Department of Health and Human
Services and the states to track several measures of economic
well-being of former welfare recipients. (Possible) By Elizabeth
Hurt
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
