<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   PILOT-FATIGUE (Washington) _ Federal Aviation Administration
officials tell Congress that they are moving to cut down on the
working hours allowed commercial airline pilots. The FAA wants to
limit pilots to 14-hour workdays and require 10-hour rest periods
between work days. Current rules don't put a ceiling on the number
of work hours and require only that pilots have eight hours off
between work days. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
<P>
   F-22-FIGHTER (Washington) _ Gen. Michael Ryan, the Air Force
chief of staff, says he is confident that the full Congress will
restore funds for the service's new multibillion fighter program,
the F-22, though the House has slashed spending for the jet. By
ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   QUAYLE-2000 (Washington) _ Former Vice President Dan Quayle
insists he's in the 2000 race to win, but polls show him far behind
other candidates and he trails in raising money. By DAN FREEDMAN.
(Also filed in the ``p'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ZAPRUDER-FILM (Dallas) _ Arbitrators declare that the government
must pay the heirs of Abraham Zapruder $16 million for the film
that Zapruder took of the assassination of President John F.
Kennedy in 1963. A Dallas historian who got a first look at the
footage just after the assassination says the film is of such
importance in American history that the price is not so outrageous.
By JIM HENDERSON.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ First Lady Hillary Clinton obviously
subscribes to former Sen. Alan Simpson's golden rule of politics:
if you're damned if you do and damned if you don't, it's best to
do. Her Talk magazine interview discussing her marriage has stirred
up a fuss but it's better to get the subject out of the way now
than have it linger close to election day when she will be in a
tight race for the New York Senate seat. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ The red-hot Houston Astros return home to
host the Los Angeles Dodgers at the Astrodome. Pitcher Mike Hampton
will go for his 15th win. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-BLINEBURY-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BKW-COMETS (Houston) _ A feature on the newest player for the
Houston Comets, Mila Nikolich. By MEGAN DICKSON.
</P>
