</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ When the SS Central America crashed 8,000 feet to the
floor of the Atlantic Ocean, 200 miles off the coast of North
Carolina in September 1857, she took 428 passengers and crew and 21
tons of gold with her. If you think it takes fiction to produce a
truly entertaining beach read, crack the spine of Gary Kinder's
``Ship of Gold in the Deep Blue Sea,'' a true account of the worst
peacetime disaster in American maritime history and of the
scientific adventurer who reclaims the ship from the bottom of the
ocean. By CAROLYN POIROT. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment
