<P>
   FBN-FALCONS _ GREENVILLE, S.C. _ News as warranted from Falcons
training camp. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BENGALS-SAWYER _ GEORGETOWN, Ky. _ Bengals left cornerback
Corey Sawyer has the coolest nickname on the team _ ``C-saw.'' But
you know what makes him hot? When people look at his
``measurables'' and either snicker, laugh or shake their heads and
walk away. The six-year veteran from Florida State admits he's not
the tallest, fastest or strongest cornerback. ``But I have a
heart,'' he said. ``I love the game. I have a desire to play
football. And that's what takes me to the next level, because I
love to compete and make plays. I think that's what makes me a
different player than the rest of the guys.'' Sawyer's back,
looking for something he doesn't get much of _ respect. (Ludwig,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BROWNS-MCNEIL _ BEREA, Ohio _ Ryan McNeil had a two-word
answer to the question about why he chose the Cleveland Browns.
``Why not?'' the highly regarded cornerback asked after taking the
practice field for the first time Monday. But surely a player in
the prime of his career, one who led the NFL with nine
interceptions for the St. Louis Rams two seasons ago, could have
found a greener pasture. Unless he knows something the
prognosticators don't. (McClelland, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-PIRATES _ PITTSBURGH _ Braves-Pirates game story.
(Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
