<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION-DIVERSITY (Undated) _ Offering a defense of
affirmative action just as it is most under attack, a Harvard
University study shows for the first time that racial diversity on
campus improves the educational experience and intellectual growth
of both minority and white students. By Kate Zernike. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   LOVE-GENERATION (Undated) _ The Free Love Generation's attitudes
toward sex haven't changed much as they start to grey, according to
a survey of sex among midlife and beyond. By Richard A. KNox. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   RICE-VITAMINS (Undated) _ Using genes from daffodills,
scientists have created a new rice that contains beta-carotene that
could address vitamin A deficiencies in Third World countries. By
Karen Hsu. 800 words.
</P>
