SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; POTPOURRI &LR;  _ One of the most difficult and
important tasks in winemaking is blending.
</P>
<P>
   Blending is at the very core of many of the world's great wines
such as Bordeaux, Champagne and California Meritage. It is sherry,
though, that stands out as the apex of the winemaking art of
blending and the solera system that makes sherry one of the world's
great under-appreciated wines.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Gerald Boyd &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR;
