<P>
   TRAVEL-SCAM (Seattle) _ More than two dozen travel companies
nationwide _ including two in the Seattle area _ are accused of
scamming consumers _ especially high school kids on spring break _
with travel packages that turned out to be nightmare trips:
bait-and-switch hotels (some had no running water, roaches, 10
people to a room), hidden charges, etc.
</P>
