   SUPPLEMENTS-CHEMO (Seattle) _ Vitamins, minerals and herbs
touted as the natural cancer-fighting compounds ``anti-oxidants''
may actually hurt cancer patients by counteracting many
chemotherapy drugs. According to two Seattle researchers _ a UW
cancer expert and a local naturopathic doctor _ who published this
finding in the July issue of Oncology (released Aug. 2), most
cancer patients today take some form of alternative therapy. With
breakout list of anti-oxidants.
