   TIMBER-RULING (Seattle) _ A judge's ruling that the federal
government broke the law in awarding nine timber contracts in the
Northwest means at least a temporary end to the logging of public
lands across much of the Pacific Northwest. Enviromentalists and
the timber industry agree that this is a huge ruling with
potentially far-reaching consequences for future logging,
particularly west of Washington state's Cascades Mountains.
</P>
<P>
   By Robert McClure. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
