helped propel George Nethercutt into office has turned against
Nethercut and may run against him becaused of Nethercutt's flipflop
on term limits. ``I'm personally hurt,'' talk show host Richard
Clear told listeners recently. ``I feel George Nethercutt let me
down as one of his biggest supporters.''
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   RAMSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ From e-mail to cell phones to debit
cards to the Net, new uses have increased the demand for telephone
time.
