<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ELVIS SCHOLARS PREPARE FOR THEIR CONVENTION
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Basking in pride that a portrait of  &UR; Elvis Presley &LR;  is hanging
in the National Portrait Gallery between  &UR; Marian Anderson &LR;  and
 &UR; Leontyne Price &LR; , Mill Valley Elvisian  &UR; Marjorie Wilkinson &LR;  is
preparing to make her way to the Fifth Annual International
Conference on Elvis Presley, which begins Friday and ends Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   This year's theme: ``Elvis in the Oval Office,'' which refers to
Presley's meeting with  &UR; Richard Nixon &LR;  on Dec. &LR;   &LR; 21, 1970. Some of
the papers to be presented at the Memphis conference:
</P>
<P>
   ``Elvis Hasn't Left the Oval Office: An American Odyssey'';
``Joined at the Hip: Birth Order, Sibling Loss and Compensation in
the Family Romance of Nixon and Elvis''; ``Mediawatch: A
Comparative Analysis of the Deaths of JFK Jr. and Elvis Presley'';
``Teaching Elvis and the American Dream in the Inner City of
Miami''; and ``George and Elvis Fanzines: Politics in the Age of
Fashion Journalism.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Suzanne Somers &LR; , hawker of the ThighMaster and the
ButtMaster, is going to be touting the FaceMaster. ``This is the
next great thing I'm bringing to America,'' she told Time magazine,
``the nonsurgical face-lift.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Noting last week's Chronicle headline in which the Falun Gong
became the Fulan Gong, China specialist  &UR; Art Zich &LR;  checked out the
meanings of the words. Fa Lun means ``wheel of law''; Fu Lan means
``rotten avariciousness.''
</P>
<P>
   _ An East Bay homeowner who bought a set of Wamsutta Elite
sheets was surprised to notice the framed photograph on the wall of
the swanky bedroom pictured on the sheet package:  &UR; Jackie &LR; 
 &UR; Kennedy &LR;  in suit and pillbox hat, on the day of the  &UR; JFK &LR; 
assassination.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOUSE AND GARDEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Sherman House in San Francisco, a Pacific Heights
bed-and-breakfast owned by  &UR; Manou Mobedshahi &LR; , is up for sale _
complete with ``furnishings and appointments'' designed by
 &UR; William Gaylord &LR;  _ for a cool $15 million.
</P>
<P>
   The very complete sales brochure for this property includes a
biography of the Coldwell Banker Realtor, &UR; Malin Giddings &LR; , noting
that she was born in Sweden and that her father was president of
the Nobel Foundation for 30 years, which is important information
for potential buyers.
</P>
<P>
   If the $15 million price tag seems high, the New York Observer
reports that  &UR; Woody Allen &LR;  and  &UR; Soon-Yi Previn &LR;  are selling his
4,000-square-foot New York penthouse for the same amount. The
apartment, which is on two stories, has a 3,500-square-foot
terrace.
</P>
<P>
   The problem, said a broker, is that the place has only one
bedroom, and the couple recently became parents. It's just not big
enough.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ACTOR'S RULES DON'T FLY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Premiere magazine describes the case of  &UR; Vin Diesel &LR; , who played
a soldier killed early on in ``Saving Private Ryan'' and had a part
in ``Reindeer Games,'' directed by  &UR; John &LR; 
 &UR; Frankenheimer &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Before shooting started, Diesel specified that he wouldn't show
his arms in the movie, because he shows them only in movies written
and directed by him. Then he wanted rewrites to make his character
more prominent.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mr. Diesel's ideas had nothing to do with the movie we were
making,'' said Frankenheimer. The ideas were completely off the
wall. And I said, `Whoa, wait just a minute. Before we start this
movie, this is the script we're doing. And we're doing it this way.
Now you either buy into that or you don't. If you don't, the best
thing for you to do is leave.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Diesel left, this time out of the action before the movie even
began.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WARM AND FUZZY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The San Francisco SPCA and San Francisco Dog Owners Group Poop
Scoop Party, on August 14 at Dolores Park, begins at 10 a.m.
(``Start picking up poops'') and ends at noon with lunch.
Meanwhile, Ringling Brothers and Barnum &AMP; Bailey, whose circus is
coming to town, has issued an elephant information packet including
a list of Animal Care Do's: ``Make sure the manure is picked up as
soon as possible.'' Meanwhile, the Independent of London explores
the theory that strict potty training in Germany ``is to blame both
for Nazism and modern thuggery.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``These days I only share my bed with my books. I wouldn't want
to live with anyone again. There would be hair and fluff and face
powder, and I don't want that about the place.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Peter O'Toole, 67, in the Times of London.
</P>
