<HEADLINE>
ELVIS SCHOLARS PREPARE FOR THEIR CONVENTION
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Basking in pride that a portrait of  &UR; Elvis Presley &LR;  is hanging
in the National Portrait Gallery between  &UR; Marian Anderson &LR;  and
 &UR; Leontyne Price &LR; , Mill Valley Elvisian  &UR; Marjorie Wilkinson &LR;  is
preparing to make her way to the Fifth Annual International
Conference on Elvis Presley, which begins Friday and ends Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   This year's theme: ``Elvis in the Oval Office,'' which refers to
Presley's meeting with  &UR; Richard Nixon &LR;  on Dec. &LR;   &LR; 21, 1970. Some of
the papers to be presented at the Memphis conference:
</P>
<P>
   ``Elvis Hasn't Left the Oval Office: An American Odyssey'';
``Joined at the Hip: Birth Order, Sibling Loss and Compensation in
the Family Romance of Nixon and Elvis''; ``Mediawatch: A
Comparative Analysis of the Deaths of JFK Jr. and Elvis Presley'';
``Teaching Elvis and the American Dream in the Inner City of
Miami''; and ``George and Elvis Fanzines: Politics in the Age of
Fashion Journalism.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Suzanne Somers &LR; , hawker of the ThighMaster and the
ButtMaster, is going to be touting the FaceMaster. ``This is the
next great thing I'm bringing to America,'' she told Time magazine,
``the nonsurgical face-lift.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Noting last week's Chronicle headline in which the Falun Gong
became the Fulan Gong, China specialist  &UR; Art Zich &LR;  checked out the
meanings of the words. Fa Lun means ``wheel of law''; Fu Lan means
``rotten avariciousness.''
</P>
<P>
   _ An East Bay homeowner who bought a set of Wamsutta Elite
sheets was surprised to notice the framed photograph on the wall of
the swanky bedroom pictured on the sheet package:  &UR; Jackie &LR; 
 &UR; Kennedy &LR;  in suit and pillbox hat, on the day of the  &UR; JFK &LR; 
assassination.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
