<HEADLINE>
SHTICK FIGURES: WE PICK WHO'S PHAT TO CHAT ON THEIR OWN SHOW
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT PHILPOT 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the 1976 movie ``Network,'' Peter Finch plays a news anchor
who has a nervous breakdown and then becomes a deranged talk-show
host. It seemed outrageous at the time, but reality is edging ever
closer, as we read the news that former porn star Traci Lords may
join the ranks of chat-show hosts.
</P>
<P>
   So many pop-culture footnotes _ Danny Bonaduce, Howie Mandel,
Carnie Wilson _ have done this that we've lost track. Thus, we've
decided to come up with the people we'd like to see host a gabfest,
along with what some of that fest would entail.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Show: ``The New Politically Incorrect With Jar Jar Binks''
</P>
<P>
   Host: Jar Jar, the much-reviled, patois-spouting comic relief
from ``The Phantom Menace''
</P>
<P>
   Sidekick: Alf, the '80s TV alien, whose shtick is eating guests'
cats
</P>
<P>
   Band: The Cantina Band from the first ``Star Wars''
</P>
<P>
   Premiere-show guests: Film critic Roger Ebert, conservative
humorist P.J. O'Rourke, the Rev. Jesse Jackson and KISS guitarist
Paul Stanley
</P>
<P>
   Sample host patter: ``Meesa no like it when you interrupt! How
rood!''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Show: ``The Samuel L. Jackson Hour''
</P>
<P>
   Host: Jackson, the don't-mess-with-me star of ``Pulp Fiction''
and ``Deep Blue Sea''
</P>
<P>
   Sidekick: Quentin Tarantino, whose shtick is saying, ``Dude,
that's so cooool!'' after every Jackson sentence
</P>
<P>
   Band: Booker T. and the MG's
</P>
<P>
   Premiere-show guests: Tim Roth, Uma Thurman, Gary Oldman and
Bridget Fonda
</P>
<P>
   Sample host patter: ``Do I look like a $%&AMP;! to you? Then why you
tryin' to %$! me like a $%!?!''
</P>
