<HEADLINE>
GOLF DAY IS NO DAY OFF FOR COWBOYS' EKUBAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By EBENEZER EKUBAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
The Cowboys' top draft pick, Ebenezer Ekuban, is writing a
training-camp diary that will appear regularly in the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram until camp breaks Aug. 25.''
\Nsubheds:Sunday, Aug. 1 Just one practice. At night, we had a
Cowboys golf social, which was real nice. I ate some fried catfish,
mashed potatoes, ribs, the normal stuff. But I was tired.
<TEXT>
<P>
   I caught the first bus back to the dorms. \Nsubheds:Monday, Aug.
2 We were off today so we could attend the Cowboys' golf classic, I
think that's what they called it. It was held at Wichita Falls
Country Club. This was my first time ever to golf. I did all right,
except everybody was scrutinizing me because I wore jeans, a
T-shirt, wide receiver gloves instead of golf gloves and football
cleats.
</P>
<P>
   All the coaches and the trainers said, ``Eb, at least look good
if you don't know how to play.'' I guess I was supposed to wear a
collared-shirt, some linen or khaki pants, golf shoes, stuff like
that. But I didn't know any better. I never golfed before.
</P>
<P>
   I never knew golf took six hours to play. By the time I got to
the ninth hole, I was slicing the ball or missing it altogether. I
was so tired. It felt like a practice. But most of the time, I was
hitting it ... not always straight, but I was hitting it.
\Nsubheds:Tuesday, Aug. 3 Defensive tackle Darren Benson asked if
he could work out with me after practice. If somebody wants to work
out extra with me, I say come on. It keeps me motivated. Plus, I
can work on my technique stuff because I have somebody simulating
an offensive lineman.
</P>
<P>
   Darren is really a great guy. From the very first day, he
greeted me with open arms. He tells me, ``Hey, rookie, you always
look like you're thinking about something. What are you thinking
about?''
</P>
<P>
   I am a rookie. Everything is new to me. So I guess I'm thinking
about all the stuff I need to learn.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
